      <h1>Task 1 - Extract Attributes</h1>

      <p>
        Additional information about attribute extraction:<br />
        <a href="https://wiki.shibboleth.net/confluence/display/SHIB2/NativeSPAddAttribute">https://wiki.shibboleth.net/confluence/display/SHIB2/NativeSPAddAttribute</a>
      </p>

      <p>
        Yesterday we learned how to release attributes on the IdP side. In this task you'll see how to reclaim and map these attributes on the receiving Service Provider side.
      </p>

      <p>
        Not surprisingly, the information for this process can be found in a file called <code>/roles/sp/templates/attribute-map.xml.j2</code>. If you open it, you'll find it to be very similiar to the attributes files seen yesterday.
      </p>

      <p>
        Add an entry for the displayName to the attribute map. You will find a corresponding entry commented out further down in the file. So, it is just a question of enabling this attribute.
      </p>
      <p>
        Provision the SP again (<code>vagrant provision</code>) and make sure that the attribute shows up after login in using the button below.
      </p>

      <p>
        Successfully finished or stuck?<br />
        Nevermind, continue to the next exercise:<br />
        <code>git checkout task2</code>
      </p>

